ixed at Overdub Lane, [[Durham, North Carolina|Durham]], [[North Carolina]]. It was engineered by [[John Plymale]] and produced by [[John Plymale|Plymale]] and Superchunk.\n\nA video was released for \"Watery Hands\" featuring actor [[David Cross]] and actress [[Janeane Garofalo]].\n\n==Track listing==\n#\"Unbelievable Things\" \u2013 5:21\n#\"Burn Last Sunday\" \u2013 4:52\n#\"Marquee\" \u2013 4:01\n#\"Watery Hands\" \u2013 4:31\n#\"Nu Bruises\" \u2013 2:41\n#\"Every Single Instinct\" \u2013 4:07\n#\"Song for Marion Brown\" \u2013 4:10\n#\"The Popular Music\" \u2013 4:04\n#\"Under Our Feet\" \u2013 3:37\n#\"European Medicine\" \u2013 5:11\n#\"Martinis on the Roof\" \u2013 5:57\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Superchunk}}\n\n[[Category:1997 albums]]\n[[Category:Superchunk albums]]\n[[Category:Merge Records albums]]\n\n{{1990s-indie-rock-album-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Indoor Living\n| type       = [[Album]]\n| artist     = [[Superchunk]]\n| cover      = Superchunk_indoor.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = September 2, 1997\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     = Echo Park Studios in [[Bloomington, Indiana|Bloomington]], [[Indiana]]\n| genre      = [[Indie rock]]\n| length     = 48:32\n| label      = [[Merge Records|Merge]]\n| producer   = [[John Plymale|Plymale]], Superchunk\n| prev_title = [[Here's Where the Strings Come In]]\n| prev_year  = 1995\n| next_title = [[Come Pick Me Up]]\n| next_year  = 1999\n}}\n\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"allmusic review\">{{cite web |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/indoor-living-mw0000595344 |title=Indoor Living \u2013 Superchunk |publisher=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=July 30, 2009 |last=Erlewine |first=Stephen Thomas |authorlink=Stephen Thomas Erlewine}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[The A.V. Club]]''\n| rev2Score = A\u2212<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://music.avclub.com/a-reissue-gives-superchunk-s-indoor-living-the-attentio-1798179573 |title=A re